<s1 id=ToStartImageVTA>To Open or Start Image Viewer
        <idx>Image Viewer, using<sort>image viewer, using<\idx>
        <idx>starting Image Viewer<sort>starting image viewer<\idx>
        <idx>opening Image Viewer<sort>opening image viewer<\idx>

<procedure>To Open Image Viewer from an Icon
<p>If Image Viewer has previously been open and the Image Viewer icon is on
the desktop, double-click the icon to open Image Viewer.

<newline>&empty;
<p gentity=ImageV-Icon gposition=left>Image Viewer Icon
<newline>&empty;

<newline>&empty;

<procedure>To Start Image Viewer from the Workspace Programs Menu
<list order>
<item>Place the mouse pointer anywhere on the background of the desktop (the
workspace) and click mouse button 3. 
<p>The Workspace menu appears.
<item>Choose Programs, and then choose Image Viewer from the Programs submenu.
<p>The Image Viewer main window appears.
<item>Choose Open from Image Viewer's File menu to open a file.
<\list>

<newline>&empty;

<procedure>To Start Image Viewer from the Front Panel
<p>If Image Viewer has been installed in the Front Panel (either directly
in the Front Panel or in the Personal Applications subpanel), click the 
Image Viewer icon to start the application.  

<p>To install Image Viewer in the Front Panel, as shown below, see
<link hyperlink="Appmanager CopyAppToFrontPanel">To Put an Application Icon
in the Front Panel<\link> in the Application Manager help volume for 
instructions.  Click Backtrack to return to this location after reading 
the instructions.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Pers-App-SubPanel>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;


<procedure>To Start Image Viewer from the Command Line
	<idx>command-line syntax<\idx>
	<idx>syntax, command-line<\idx>
	<idx>sdtimage<\idx>
	<idx>starting Image Viewer<sort>starting image viewer<\idx>
	<idx>opening file using Image Viewer<sort>opening file using image viewer<\idx>

<p>You can start Image Viewer and open files directly from the command line.

<list bullet>
<item>Type <computer>sdtimage<\computer> to start Image Viewer.

<item>Type <computer>sdtimage<\computer> <emph>filename<\emph> to start Image Viewer 
and open a specific file.

<item>Type <computer>sdtimage -snapshot<\computer> to start Image Viewer
Snapshot when you start Image Viewer. 

<\list>

<newline>&empty;

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet>
<item> <xref ToExitImageVTA>
<item> <xref ToOpenAnImageFileTA>
<item> <xref ToViewADocumentFileTA>
<item> <xref ToStartSnapshotTA> 
<\list>


