<s1 id=ToRotateImageTA>To Rotate an Image
	<idx>images, rotating<\idx>
	<idx>rotating images<\idx>

You can rotate an image by clicking on one of the tilted teapots in
the top-right panel of the Image Viewer Palette. 

<list order>
<item> Display the Image Viewer Palette by choosing Palette from the
Edit menu.
<item>Specify the number of degrees you want the image or page rotated in the 
Rotate Degrees field in the palette.

<p>The default value is 90 degrees; change the value in one of the
following ways:

<list bullet tight> 
<item>Double-click on the number in the Rotate Degrees field and type
the desired number.
<item> Click the arrow buttons to change the rotation number up or down. 
<item> Drag the slider right or left to raise or lower the number.
<\list> 

<!-- <p gentity=ImageV-Rotate-Tool gposition=left> -->
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Rotate-Tool>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<item>Click one of the rotate tools to rotate the image or page
left or right.
<p>Image Viewer rotates the image or page according to the value 
in the Rotate Degrees field.

<item> If you want to restore the image to its last-saved orientation, click
Revert. 
<\list>

<newline> &empty; 
<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToUndoEditOperationTA>
<item> <xref ToScaleImageTA>
<item> <xref ToFlipImageTA>
<item> <xref ImageVPaletteDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToFlipImageTA>To Flip an Image
	<idx>images, flipping<\idx>
	<idx>flipping images<\idx>

<list order>
<item> Display the Image Viewer Palette by choosing Palette from the
Edit menu.
<item>Click one of the flip tools to invert or create a mirror image of the
currently displayed image or page.
<item> If you want to restore the image to its last-saved orientation, click
Revert. 
<\list>

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Flip-Tool>
