<s1 id=ToScaleImageTA>To Scale an Image
	<idx>scaling images<\idx>
	<idx>scale image<\idx>
	<idx>images, scaling<\idx>
	<idx>image, to scale<\idx>

<p>To change the magnification of the View window:
<list order>
<item> Display the Image Viewer Palette by choosing Palette from the
Edit menu.
<item>Specify the percentage of magnification in the Scale Percentage field.
<p>Click in the Scale Percentage field and type the number, click the arrow
buttons, or drag the slider to change the percentage of magnification.

<!-- <p gentity=ImageV-Zoom-Tool gposition=left> -->
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Zoom-Tool>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<item>Click the Scale tool.
<p>Image Viewer increases or decreases (scales up or down) the 
magnification of the image in 
the View window according to the value you have entered.
<item> If you want to restore the image to its last-saved orientation, click
Revert. 
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToUndoEditOperationTA>
<item> <xref ToFlipImageTA>
