<s1 id=ToUndoEditOperationTA>To Undo an Edit Operation
	<idx>edit operation, undoing<\idx>
	<idx>undoing an edit operation<\idx>

Image Viewer provides two methods of cancelling an unsaved edit operation:

<list bullet>
<item>Choose Undo from the Edit menu
to cancel the <emph>last unsaved edit<\emph> made to an image or page.

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Edit-Undo>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<item>Click the Revert button on the palette
to cancel <emph>all unsaved<\emph> changes and display the last saved 
version of the image or page.

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Palette-Revert>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<\list>

