<s1 id=ToSaveEditedImageSameFileTA>To Save an Edited Image in the Same File
	<idx>image, saving edited<\idx>
	<idx>saving an edited image<\idx>

<p>To save changes you've made to an image or page in the same file you opened:
<list order>
<item>Choose Save from the File menu.
<p>The Save dialog box appears.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Save-Dialog>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<item>Click OK.
<p>A warning dialog box is displayed, giving you the option to
overwrite the existing file or to cancel the save operation.
<item>Click Overwrite Existing File to save the file with the same name.
<p>Image Viewer overwrites the existing file with the current contents of 
the View window.
<p>Click Cancel if you do not want to overwrite the existing file;
change the file name or change folders in the Save dialog box to save
the changes to a new file. 
<\list>
<newline>&empty;

