<s1 id=ToSelectAreaToSaveTA>To Select a Region to Save as a New File
	<idx>saving region of image in new file<\idx>
	<idx>selecting region of image to save in new file<\idx>
	<idx>new file, saving region of image in<\idx>
	<idx>region of image, saving in new file<\idx>
	<idx>images, saving region in new file<\idx>

<p>You can cut out a region of
an image or page and save that region as a new file.
<list order>
<item>Click the Selector tool in the palette.

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Selector-Tool>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<item>Move the pointer into the View window.
<item>Place the target pointer over a corner of the region you want to save 
as a new image and drag mouse button 1 to the opposite corner.

<newline>&empty;

<!-- need to find a good image for this illustration -->

<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Selected-Image>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;
<p>Image Viewer draws a border around the region you define.
<item>Choose Save Selection As from the File menu.
<p>The Save Selection As dialog box appears.
<item>Choose the path, file format, compression method, colors, and file name.
<item>Click OK.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToSaveEditedImageSameFileTA> 
<item> <xref ToSaveImageNewFileTA>
<item> <xref ImageVSaveSelectionAsDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToSaveImageNewFileTA>To Save an Image as a New File
	<idx>images, saving<\idx>
	<idx>saving images, in new files<\idx>

<p>To save a file and specify its format, folder, and name: 
<list order>
<item>Choose Save As from the File menu.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-SaveAs-Dialog>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<item>Double-click a folder name in the Folder list to open it.
<item>Type the name of the file in the Enter file name field.
<item>Select the file format in which you want your file written.
<p>For a list of formats, see <link hyperlink=ImageVFileFormats Definition>Image
Viewer File Formats<\link>.
<item>Choose a compression method from the 
Compression menu button.
<p>The default is None (no compression); compressed files require less disk space.
<item>Choose the number of colors to save for your file from the
Colors menu button.  
The choices depend on the type of monitor you have.
<item>Click OK.
<p>Image Viewer saves your file in the specified format.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToSelectAreaToSaveTA>
<item> <xref ToSaveEditedImageSameFileTA>
<item> <xref ImageVSaveSelectionAsDialog>
<item> <xref ImageVFileMenu>
<item> <xref ImageVFileFormats>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToSaveSinglePageNewFileTA>To Save a Single Page as a New File
	<idx>saving, single page in a new file<\idx>
	<idx>single page, saving in a new file<\idx>

<newline>&empty;
<p>To save the currently displayed page in a new file:
<list order>
<item>Choose Save Page As Image from the File menu.
<p>Image Viewer displays a dialog box similar to the Save As dialog box.
<item>Either type a path in the Enter path or folder name field or
double-click folder names in the Folders list to navigate to the
folder in which you want to save the new file.
<item>Type the name for the file in the Enter file name field.
<item>Select a file format.
<item>Click OK.
<p>Image Viewer creates the new file.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ImageVSaveAsDialog>
<item> <xref ToSaveImageNewFileTA>
<item> <xref ImageVFileMenu>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToPreviewFileTA>To Preview a File to Be Printed
	<idx>files, previewing before printing<\idx>
	<idx>previewing files before printing<\idx>

<p>The Print Preview window shows how the contents of the View window will 
appear when printed with the current Print dialog box settings.
<list order>
<item>Choose Print Preview from the File menu.
<p>The Print Preview dialog box is displayed. 

<newline>&empty;
<!-- <p gentity=ImageV-Print-Preview gposition=left> -->
<!-- <newline>&empty; -->
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Print-Preview>
<\figure>

<p>If the image is too big to fit on a single page, lines in the Print
Preview window show you the boundaries of the printed page.

<item>To control which area of the image or page is printed, move the
pointer into the window (it changes to a hand shape) and drag the
image into position.

<item>To print the image, click Print in the Print Preview dialog box
and then click Print in the Print dialog box that is displayed.

<p> See <xref ImageVPrintPreviewDialog> for information obout print
settings. 

<item>Click Close to close the Print Preview dialog box.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToPrintSingleCopyTA>
<item> <xref ImageVPrintDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToPrintSingleCopyTA>To Print a Single Copy
	<idx>single copy, printing<\idx>
	<idx>printing, single copy<\idx>

<p>To print a single copy of the image or multiple-page document you
are viewing:
<list bullet>
<item>Choose Print One from the File menu.
<p>Image Viewer prints one copy of the file, using the current Print 
dialog box settings.  See <xref ImageVPrintDialog> for information about
Print settings.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
