<s1 id=ToSnapWindowTA> To Take a Snapshot of a Window
	<idx>Snapshot:taking snapshot of window<sort>snapshot:taking snapshot of window<\idx>
        <idx>taking snapshot of window<\idx>
        <idx>window, taking snapshot<\idx>

<list order>

<item> If Snapshot is not running, choose Snapshot from the Image
Viewer File menu. 

<item> Click the Window radio box at the top of the Snapshot window.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Snapshot-Window-ButSel>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<item> Click the Snap button at the bottom of the Snapshot dialog box.

<p> The mouse pointer becomes a plus sign.

<item> Move the mouse pointer to the window to be snapped and click
mouse button 1. 

<p> The message at the bottom of the Snapshot dialog box reads "Snap
succeeded" once the window is snapped.

<p> You can now save or print the captured image, edit the image with
the Image View Palette, or take another snapshot which will replace
the current image.

<\list> 

