<s1 id=ToSnapRegionTA> To Take a Snapshot of a Region
        <idx>taking snapshot of region<\idx>
	<idx>Snapshot:taking snapshot of region<sort>snapshot:taking snapshot of region<\idx>
	<idx>region, taking snapshot<\idx>

<list order>
<item> If Snapshot is not running, choose Snapshot from the Image
Viewer File menu. 

<item> Click the Region radio box at the top of the Snapshot dialog box.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Snapshot-Region-ButSel>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<item> Click the Snap button at the bottom of the Snapshot dialog box.

<p> The mouse pointer becomes a plus sign.

<item> Move the mouse pointer to a corner of the region to be snapped,
press and hold mouse button 1, drag the mouse diagonally to encompass
the region to be snapped, and release mouse button 1.

<p> The message at the bottom of the Snapshot dialog box reads "Snap
succeeded" once the region is snapped.

<p> You can now save or print the captured image, edit the image with
the Image View Palette, or take another snapshot which will replace
the current image.

