<s1 id=ToTakeDelayedSnapTA> To Take a Delayed Snapshot 
	<idx>Snapshot:taking delayed snapshot<sort>snapshot:taking delayed<\idx>
	<idx>delayed snapshot, taking<\idx>
	<idx>Snapshot:Snapshot Delay Setting<sort>snapshot:snapshot delay<\idx>
	<idx>Snapshot Delay Setting<sort>snapshot delay setting<\idx>
	<idx>Delay Setting, Snapshot<sort>delay setting, snapshot<\idx>

When taking a snapshot of a menu or some other popup or pulldown
element, you can delay the time between clicking Snap and the snapshot
being taken by changing the Snapshot Delay setting.

<list order>
<item> If Snapshot is not running, choose Snapshot from the Image
Viewer File menu. 

<item>Click the Snap Delay down arrow, select the number of seconds
for the delay, and release the mouse button.

<p>Or, click in the text field and type the number of seconds for the
delay.  

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=ImageV-Snapshot-DelayPopdown>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<p> The next time you click Snap, the snapshot will be delayed by
the specified number of seconds.

<item> <emph>Optional.<\emph> If you want to hear the seconds counted off before the snapshot
is taken, select the Beep During Countdown checkbox. 

<item> Select a Snap Type and click Snap. 

<p> If Snap Type is Region, drag mouse button 1 to
select the region to be snapped.

<item> Make necessary adjustments to the image during the snap delay time.

<p> You can display a menu, for instance, by clicking on an item in a
menu bar. 

<p> After the specified number of seconds, the window, region, or
screen is snapped and "Snap succeeded" is displayed in the
message area at the bottom of the window.

<\list> 

<procedure> See Also 
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ImageVSnapshotWindow> 
<item> <xref ToHideSnapTA> 
<\list>


<s1 id=ToHideSnapTA> To Hide the Snapshot Dialog Box While Taking a Snapshot
	<idx>Snapshot:hiding Snapshot dialog box<sort>snapshot:hiding<\idx>
	<idx>hiding Snapshot dialog box<\idx>

If you want a snapshot of the entire screen and do not want the
Snapshot dialog box to be included in the image, you can hide the
Snapshot dialog box while you take a snapshot.

<list order>
<item> If Snapshot is not running, choose Snapshot from the Image
Viewer File menu. 

<item> Select the Hide Window During Capture checkbox. 

<p> The Snap Delay changes to 8 seconds and the message area at the
bottom of the Snapshot dialog box displays: "Timer adjusted to
guarantee correct operation."

<item> Click Snap to take a snapshot.

<p> All Image Viewer windows disappear and do not reappear until after
the snapshot has been taken.

<\list> 

